Pakistan’s Overseas, Domestic Cement Sales Decline in May

-- B y   K h u r r u m   A n i s
-- 
2011-06-03T09:30:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-03/pakistan-s-overseas-domestic-cement-sales-decline-in-may.html
Pakistan ’s overseas shipments and
domestic sales of cement declined in May as construction slowed.  Cement makers sold 1.9 million metric tons of cement in the
local market in May, compared with 2.1 million tons a year ago,
according to data posted on the  website  of the All-Pakistan
Cement Manufacturers Association. Exports fell to 875,955 tons
from 957,481 tons a year earlier.  Overseas sales fell 12.5 percent to 8.5 million tons during
the 11 months ended May 31 and local sales declined 7.1 percent
to 19.9 million tons, according to the data.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Khurrum Anis in Karachi at 
